-- Guinea's Government Wants 20% of Rio Tinto's Simandou Blocks 3 and 4
-- Alpha Camara
-- 2010-06-24T07:37:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/guinea-s-government-wants-20-of-rio-tinto-s-simandou-blocks-3-and-4.html

          
          
             Guinea’s government sent Rio Tinto
Group a letter yesterday informing the company of its intention
to acquire a 20 percent stake in blocks 3 and 4 of the Simandou
iron ore concession.  
 Guinea has the rights to buy the stake, Mahmoud Thiam, the
country’s mines minister, said in an interview in Conakry late
yesterday.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
